Manager (Purple)

Managers with strong training skills play a crucial role in fostering a learning culture within their department and the organization. They exhibit the training soft skill by developing comprehensive training programs, allocating resources for professional development, and supporting employees in their training endeavors. Managers actively engage with their team to assess training needs and ensure that the team has access to the necessary training resources. They actively promote a culture of continuous learning and knowledge-sharing within the department. Examples at this level may include creating a learning and development roadmap for the team, organizing cross-functional training sessions, or providing financial support for employees to attend industry conferences.
